---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Core Concepts">
  <h1>Core Concepts</h1>

  <h2>Nodes</h2>
  <p>Nodes are the primary entities. Each node has a type (defined by <code>NodeTypeDef</code>), a payload (typed fields), an owner, and ACL configuration.</p>
  <pre is:raw><code># Types are defined once in schema.py with stable numeric IDs
Task = NodeTypeDef(type_id=1, name="Task", fields=(
    field(1, "title", "str", required=True),
    field(2, "status", "enum", enum_values=("todo", "done")),
))</code></pre>
  <p>The <code>type_id</code> and <code>field_id</code> numbers are immutable. Names can change, IDs cannot.</p>

  <h2>Edges</h2>
  <p>Edges are unidirectional relationships between nodes. Edge types define which node types can be connected:</p>
  <pre is:raw><code>AssignedTo = EdgeTypeDef(edge_id=1, name="AssignedTo",
    from_type=Task, to_type=User,
    propagate_share=False)  # assigning doesn't share ACL

HasComment = EdgeTypeDef(edge_id=2, name="HasComment",
    from_type=Task, to_type=Comment,
    propagate_share=True)   # sharing task shares comments</code></pre>
  <p><code>propagate_share=True</code> makes the edge "structural" &mdash; child nodes inherit access from the parent.</p>

  <h2>Tenants</h2>
  <p>Every operation requires a <code>tenant_id</code>. Each tenant gets its own SQLite database file. Tenants are fully isolated &mdash; no cross-tenant queries.</p>
  <pre is:raw><code># Different tenants, completely separate data
plan_acme = db.atomic("acme", "user:alice")
plan_globex = db.atomic("globex", "user:bob")</code></pre>

  <h2>Actors</h2>
  <p>Every operation requires an <code>actor</code> &mdash; the identity performing the action. Format: <code>type:id</code>.</p>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Actor</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    <tr><td><code>user:alice</code></td><td>Specific user</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>group:eng</code></td><td>Group identity</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>system:applier</code></td><td>System/service account</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>tenant:*</code></td><td>Wildcard &mdash; all users in tenant</td></tr>
  </table>

  <h2>Event Sourcing</h2>
  <p>Writes are never applied directly to SQLite. They follow this path:</p>
  <ol>
    <li><code>plan.commit()</code> &rarr; operations serialized as a transaction event</li>
    <li>Event appended to WAL (Kafka, Kinesis, Pub/Sub, SQS, etc.)</li>
    <li>Server returns <code>Receipt</code> with <code>stream_position</code></li>
    <li>Applier consumes WAL events, applies them to SQLite idempotently</li>
    <li>Reads come from SQLite (eventually consistent, or use <code>after_offset</code> for immediate consistency)</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Atomic Transactions (Plan)</h2>
  <p>Multiple operations are batched into a single atomic transaction via the <code>Plan</code> builder:</p>
  <pre is:raw><code>plan = db.atomic("acme", "user:alice")
plan.create(Task, {"title": "New Task"}, as_="task")
plan.create(Comment, {"body": "First comment"}, as_="comment")
plan.edge_create(HasComment, from_="$task.id", to="$comment.id")
result = await plan.commit()
# All three operations succeed or fail together</code></pre>
  <p>The <code>as_</code> parameter creates an alias for referencing the created node in subsequent operations (<code>$task.id</code>).</p>

  <h2>Read-after-Write Consistency</h2>
  <p>By default, reads are eventually consistent (SQLite may lag behind the WAL). For immediate consistency after a write:</p>
  <pre is:raw><code># Option 1: Wait during commit
result = await plan.commit(wait_applied=True)

# Option 2: Wait on specific read
task = await db.get(Task, node_id, "acme", "user:alice",
                    after_offset=result.receipt.stream_position)</code></pre>

  <h2>Schema Registry</h2>
  <p>Type definitions are registered in a <code>SchemaRegistry</code>. The registry generates a fingerprint (SHA-256 hash) used for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Deployment safety</strong>: server rejects writes with mismatched fingerprint</li>
    <li><strong>CI checks</strong>: <code>entdb check</code> validates compatibility before deploy</li>
    <li><strong>Schema evolution</strong>: tracks what changed between versions</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
